Description: Object made of unfired brown clay, relatively flat and rounded in the shape of a cartouche with the upper part, left side and lower part broken off. Hieroglyphs in sunken relief, visible are the legs of an animal, underneath mrj, followed by two further horizontal signs n and nb? The rear is uneven without any original surface preserved. Stamped cartouche that might have been used in architecture like wall plaster? It is clearly not a stamped brick as the rounded cartouche-shape is preserved on the outer right side.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
